    Settings of fromcode and tocode and their permitted combinations are
    implementation-dependent. The following codesets are supported:

    *     ASCII
    *     EUC-JP
    *     eucJP
    *     SJIS
    *     Unicode
    *     windows-932

    (EUC-JP and eucJP are identical; SJIS and windows-932 are also identical.)

    A conversion descriptor remains valid in a process until that process
    closes it.

    If a file descriptor is used to implement conversion descriptors, the
    FD_CLOEXEC flag will be set (defined in <fcntl.h>).

    The arguments are:

    tocode
